HEADWORD: Gypsum
<hw>Gyp"sum</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧p"s⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>gypsum</ets>, Gr. <grk>gy`psos</grk>; cf. Ar. <ets>jibs</ets>
plaster, mortar, Per. <ets>jabs⟦imac⟧n</ets> lime.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral consisting of the hydrous sulphate of
lime (calcium). When calcined, it forms plaster of Paris.
<stype>Selenite</stype> is a transparent, crystalline variety;
<stype>alabaster</stype>, a fine, white, massive variety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gypsy</ent>⟦br⟧
